	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Thanks for all the hard work creating all these music rips!  However, I have one issue that bugs me to no end.  Not all games that support stereo sound are ripped in stereo!
<br />For example, Pokemon Yellow supports Mono, Earphone1, Earphone2, and Earphone3 audio modes.  The rip is only Mono.  Could someone please rip this game in stereo (at least Earphone1 mode, but a separate rip for each mode would be wonderful!) or tell me how to do it myself (if it's a simple fix...)
<br />
<br />Also, I notice that in many songs in Yellow the Noise channel is sporadic and extremely messed up with all the GBS players I use.  (foo_gep, NEZPlug, etc)
<br />
<br />Pokemon Crystal has Mono and Stereo audio modes and the rip is only in Mono.  This game NEEDS stereo!  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_surprised.gif" alt=":o" title="Surprised" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


